cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new segmentation model using a recurrent neural network, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV). The model is trained using limited data, which is a common challenge in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the optimization of intermediate steps in the segmentation process, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a neural network for segmentation also falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to cardiac MRI images, which is a common application in medical imaging (cs.MM).
